obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (96652)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, commencement and application.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96652&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Boilers Act, 2025.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date1^`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act and any reference`
  line `in any provision to the commencement of this Act shall be construed as a reference to the coming into force`
  line `of that provision.`
  line
  line `(3) Save as otherwise expressly provided, the provisions of this Act shall apply to all boilers and boiler`
  line `components including boilers and boiler components belonging to the Central Government and the State`
  line Governments.
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this Act shall apply to---`
  line
  line `(a) locomotive boilers belonging to or under the control of the railways;`
  line
  line `(b) any boiler or boiler components,---`
  line
  line `(i) in any vessel propelled wholly or in part by the agency of steam;`
  line
  line `(ii) belonging to or under the control of the Army, Navy or Air Force; or`
  line
  line `(iii) appertaining to a sterilizer or disinfector used in hospitals or nursing homes, if the boiler`
  line `does not exceed one hundred litres in capacity.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st day of May, 2025, vide notification No. S.O. 1943 (E), dated 30th day of April, 2025, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3 (ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (96653)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96653&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `(a) "accident" means an explosion of boiler or boiler components, which is calculated to weaken`
  line `the strength or an uncontrolled release of water or steam therefrom, liable to cause death or injury to`
  line `any person or damage to any property;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means the Central Boilers Board constituted under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "boiler" means a pressure vessel in which steam is generated for use external to itself by`
  line `application of heat which is wholly or partly under pressure when steam is shut off but does not include`
  line `a pressure vessel,---`
  line
  line `(i) with capacity less than twenty-five litres, such capacity being measured from the feed check`
  line `valve to the main steam stop valve; or`
  line
  line `(ii) with less than one kilogram per centimetre square design gauge pressure and working gauge`
  line `pressure; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in which water is heated below one hundred degrees centigrade;`
  line
  line `(d) "boiler components" means steam piping, feed piping, economiser, superheater, any mounting`
  line `or other fitting and any other external or internal part of a boiler which is subject to pressure exceeding`
  line `one kilogram per centimetre square gauge.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- For the purposes of this clause, the term "superheater" means any equipment which`
  line `is partly or wholly exposed to flue gases for the purpose of raising the temperature of steam beyond the`
  line `saturation temperature at that pressure and includes a re-heater;`
  line
  line `(e) "Chief Inspector", "Deputy Chief Inspector" and "Inspector", mean, respectively, a person`
  line `appointed to be a Chief Inspector, a Deputy Chief Inspector and an Inspector under section 5;`
  line
  line `(f) "competent authority" means an institution referred to in sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(g) "competent person" means an inspector or a person recognised in such manner as may be`
  line `specified by regulations, for inspection and certification of boilers and boiler components during`
  line `manufacture, erection and use;`
  line
  line `(h) "economiser" means any part of a feed-pipe that is wholly or partially exposed to the action of`
  line `flue gases for the purpose of recovery of waste heat;`
  line
  line `(i) "feed-pipe" means any pipe or connected fitting wholly or partly under pressure through which`
  line `feed water passes directly to a boiler and which does not form an integral part thereof;`
  line
  line `(j) "inspecting authority" means a chief inspector or an institution recognised in such manner as`
  line `may be specified by regulations, for the inspection and certification of boilers and boiler components`
  line `during manufacture and erection;`
  line
  line `(k) "manufacture" means manufacture, construction and fabrication of boiler or boiler components,`
  line `or both;`
  line
  line `(l) "manufacturer" means a person engaged in the manufacture of boiler or boiler components, or`
  line both;
  line
  line `(m) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(n) "owner" includes any person possessing or using a boiler as agent of the owner thereof and any`
  line `person using a boiler which he has hired or obtained on loan from the owner thereof;`
  line
  line `(o) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(p) "regulations" means regulations made by the Board under section 40;`
  line
  line `(q) "State Government" shall include Union territory administration;`
  line
  line `(r) "steam-pipe" means any pipe through which steam passes, if---`
  line
  line `(i) the pressure at which steam passes through such pipe exceeds three and half kilogram per`
  line `square centimeters above atmospheric pressure; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such pipe exceeds two hundred fifty-four millimeters in internal diameter and the pressure`
  line `of steam exceeds one kilogram per square centimeters above the atmospheric pressure,`
  line
  line `and includes in either case, any connected fitting of a steam-pipe and feed-pipe;`
  line
  line `(s) "structural alteration, addition or renewal" means,---`
  line
  line `(i) any change in the design of a boiler or boiler components;`
  line
  line `(ii) replacement of any part of boiler or boiler components by a part which does not conform`
  line `to the same specification; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any addition to any part of a boiler or boiler components;`
  line
  line `(t) "Technical Adviser" means the Technical Adviser appointed under sub-section (1) of section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (96654)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Central Boilers Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96654&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, constitute a Board to`
  line `be called the Central Boilers Board, for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board shall consist of the following members, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the Secretary to the Government of India in charge of the Department having administrative`
  line `control of the Board who shall be the Chairperson, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(b) one member to represent each State, other than Union territory, who shall be a senior technical`
  line `officer conversant with the inspection and examination of boilers, to be nominated by that State`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(c) members, equal in number to members nominated under clause (b), to be nominated by the Central Government, to represent the following, namely:---`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Bureau of Indian Standards;`
  line
  line `(iii) boiler and boiler components manufactures;`
  line
  line `(iv) National laboratories;`
  line
  line `(v) engineering consultancy agencies;`
  line
  line `(vi) users of boilers; and`
  line
  line `(vii) such other interests which, in the opinion of the Central Government, ought to be`
  line `represented on the Board;`
  line
  line `(d) Technical Adviser, who shall be the Member-Secretary, ex officio.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of the members nominated under clauses (b) and (c) of sub-section (2), and the`
  line `manner of their nomination, shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The Board may determine its own procedure for the conduct of all business to be transacted by it.`
  line
  line `(5) The Board shall have power to constitute committees and sub-committees from amongst its`
  line `members and to delegate any of its powers and duties to such committees or sub-committees.`
  line
  line `(6) The powers of the Board may be exercised notwithstanding any vacancy in the Board.`
  line
  line `(7) The functions of the Board shall be to regulate the design, manufacture, erection and use of boiler`
  line `and boiler components to ensure safety of life and property of persons from the danger of explosions of`
  line `steam-boilers and for uniformity in registration and inspection and for these purposes, make such`
  line `regulations as it deems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (96655)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Technical Adviser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96655&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, by notification, appoint a Technical`
  line `Adviser from amongst the persons having such qualifications and experience as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The salary and allowances and other terms and conditions of service of the Technical Adviser shall`
  line `be such as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The Technical Adviser shall, in addition to exercising the powers and discharging the functions`
  line `assigned to him under this Act and the rules and regulations made thereunder, exercise such other powers`
  line `and discharge such functions as the Central Government and the Board may delegate to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (96656)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Chief Inspector, Deputy Chief Inspector and Inspector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96656&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may appoint`
  line `such persons as it thinks fit to be Inspectors for the State for the purposes of this Act and may define the`
  line `local limits within which each Inspector shall exercise the powers and perform the duties conferred and`
  line `imposed on Inspectors by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may appoint such persons as it thinks fit to be Deputy Chief Inspectors for`
  line `the State and may define the local limits within which each Deputy Chief Inspector shall exercise powers`
  line `and perform duties under this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) A Deputy Chief Inspector may exercise the powers and perform the duties conferred and imposed`
  line `on an Inspector by or under this Act and, in addition thereto, may exercise such powers or perform such`
  line `duties conferred or imposed on the Chief Inspector by or under this Act, as the State Government may`
  line `assign to him.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government shall appoint a person to be the Chief Inspector for the State who may, in`
  line `addition to the powers and duties conferred and imposed on a Chief Inspector by or under this Act, exercise`
  line `any power or perform any duty so conferred or imposed on Deputy Chief Inspectors or Inspectors.`
  line
  line `(5) No person shall be appointed as a Chief Inspector, or Deputy Chief Inspectors or Inspectors, unless`
  line `he possesses such qualifications and experience as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Deputy Chief Inspectors and Inspectors shall exercise the`
  line `powers and perform the duties conferred and imposed on them by or under this Act under the general`
  line `superintendence and control of the Chief Inspector.`
  line
  line `(7) The Chief Inspector, Deputy Chief Inspectors and Inspectors may offer such advice as they think`
  line `fit to the owners regarding the proper maintenance and safe working of boilers.`
  line
  line `(8) The Chief Inspector, Deputy Chief Inspectors and Inspectors shall exercise such other powers and`
  line `duties as may be prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(9) The Chief Inspector, Deputy Chief Inspectors and Inspectors shall be deemed to be public servants`
  line `within the meaning of clause (28) of section 2 of the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita, 2023 (45 of 2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (96657)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Competent authority to grant welders certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96657&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The competent authority shall be an`
  line `institution recognised in such manner as may be specified by regulations, for grant of certificate to the`
  line `welders for welding of boiler and boiler components.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who intends to undertake any welding work connected with or related to a boiler or a`
  line `boiler component, or both, shall apply to the competent authority for the grant of such welders certificate`
  line `as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application under sub-section (2), the competent authority shall follow such`
  line `procedure for examination and grant of welders certificate as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) The competent authority may, if satisfied that the person applying for welders certificate under`
  line `sub-section (2) has complied with the conditions for the grant of the welders certificate, grant such`
  line `certificate, subject to such other conditions and on payment of such fee, as may be specified by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority shall not refuse such certificate to any person unless the person`
  line `is given an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (96658)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Conditions precedent for manufacture of boiler and boiler components.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96658&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No person shall`
  line `manufacture or cause to be manufactured any boiler or boiler components, or both, unless---`
  line
  line `(a) the premises or precincts wherein boiler or boiler components, or both, are manufactured, have`
  line `such facilities for design and construction as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(b) a certificate for the design and drawings of the boiler and boiler components have been granted`
  line `by the inspecting authority under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(c) the material, mounting and fitting used in the construction of boiler or boiler components, or`
  line `both, conform to such specifications as may be specified by regulations; and`
  line
  line `(d) the person engaged in welding boiler or boiler components hold welders certificate granted by`
  line `the competent authority under sub-section (4) of section 6.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (96659)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Inspection during manufacture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96659&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every manufacturer, before commencing manufacture of a`
  line `boiler or boiler components, shall engage an inspecting authority for carrying out inspection at such stages`
  line `of manufacture as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) The inspecting authority engaged under sub-section (1) shall follow such procedure for inspection`
  line `and certification of boiler or boiler components as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Where, after inspection, the inspecting authority---`
  line
  line `(a) is satisfied that the design and drawings of the boiler or the boiler components conforms to the`
  line `standards as may be specified by regulations, it shall grant a certificate of inspection and stamp the`
  line `boiler or boiler components, or both; or`
  line
  line `(b) is of the opinion that the boiler or boiler components, or both, does not conform to such`
  line `standards as may be specified by regulations, it may for reasons to be recorded in writing, refuse to`
  line `grant such certificate:`
  line
  line `Provided that no certificate shall be refused unless the inspecting authority has directed the`
  line `manufacturer of the boiler or boiler components, or both, in writing to carry out such modifications or`
  line `rectifications as it deems necessary and the inspecting authority is of the opinion that inspite of such`
  line `direction, the manufacturer of the boiler or boiler components, or both, has not carried out the`
  line `modifications or rectifications.`
  line
  line `(4) The inspecting authority may, for the purposes of inspection under this section, charge such fee as`
  line `may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (96660)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Inspection during erection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96660&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any owner who intends to register a boiler under section 12, shall`
  line `engage an inspecting authority for carrying out inspection at the stage of erection of the boiler.`
  line
  line `(2) The inspecting authority shall follow such procedure for inspection and certification of a boiler or`
  line `boiler components, or both, as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(3) Where, after inspection, the inspecting authority---`
  line
  line `(a) is satisfied that the erection of the boiler is in accordance with such standards as may be`
  line `specified by regulations, it shall grant a certificate of inspection in such form as may be specified by`
  line `regulations; or`
  line
  line `(b) is of the opinion that the boiler has not been erected in accordance with such regulations, it may`
  line `for reasons to be recorded in writing, refuse to grant the certificate and shall communicate such refusal`
  line `to the owner and the manufacturer of the boiler or boiler components forthwith:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such certificate shall be refused unless the inspecting authority has directed the owner`
  line `in writing to carry out such modifications or rectifications as it deems necessary and the inspecting authority`
  line `is of the opinion that in spite of such direction, the owner has not carried out the modifications or`
  line rectifications.
  line
  line `(4) The inspecting authority may, for the purposes of inspection under this section, charge such fee as`
  line `may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (96661)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Conditions precedent for repairing boiler and boiler components.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96661&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall repair`
  line `or cause to be repaired boiler or boiler components, or both, unless---`
  line
  line `(a) the premises or precincts, wherein boiler or boiler components or both, are being used has such`
  line `facilities for repairs as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(b) the design and drawings of the boiler or boiler components conform to such standards, and the`
  line `material, mounting and fitting used in the repair of boiler or boiler components, conform to such`
  line `specifications as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(c) persons engaged in welding, holds a welders certificate granted by the competent authority`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) the user who does not have the in-house facilities for repair of boiler or boiler components,`
  line `engages a boiler repairer possessing a boiler repairer certificate;`
  line
  line `(e) the user engage a competent person for approval of repairs to be carried out in-house or by the`
  line repairers;
  line
  line `(f) the safety of persons working inside a boiler is ensured, by taking such measures, as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) A boiler repairer shall obtain such certificate in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (96662)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Prohibition of use of unregistered or uncertified boiler.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96662&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly`
  line `provided in this Act, no owner of a boiler shall use the boiler or permit it to be used,---`
  line
  line `(a) unless it has been registered in accordance with the provisions of this Act or the rules or`
  line `regulations made thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) any boiler which has been transferred from one State to another, until the transfer has been`
  line `reported in such manner as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(c) unless the owner is in possession of the certificate or the provisional order authorising the use`
  line `of the boiler;`
  line
  line `(d) at a pressure higher than the maximum pressure recorded in such certificate or provisional order;`
  line
  line `(e) where the Central Government has made rules requiring that boiler shall be in the charge of`
  line `persons holding certificates of proficiency or competency, unless the boiler is in the charge of a person`
  line `holding the certificate required by such rules:`
  line
  line `Provided that any boiler registered, or any boiler certified or licensed, under any Act herebefore`
  line `repealed, shall be deemed to have been registered or certified, as the case may be, under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The qualification and experience of persons intending to obtain a certificate of proficiency or`
  line `competency, fee and the procedure for obtaining such certificate, shall be such as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (96663)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title Registration.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96663&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The owner of a boiler which is not registered under the provisions of this Act`
  line `shall make an application to the Inspector in such form, along with such drawings, specification, certificate`
  line `and other documents as may be specified by regulations, to have the boiler registered.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for registration under sub-section (1) shall be accompanied by such fee as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1), the Inspector shall fix a date, within thirty days or`
  line `such shorter period as may be prescribed by the State Government, from the date of the receipt of the application,`
  line `for examination of the boiler and shall give the owner thereof not less than ten days notice of the date so fixed.`
  line
  line `(4) On the date so fixed under sub-section (3), the Inspector shall inspect the boiler with a view to satisfying`
  line `himself that the boiler has not suffered any damage during its transit from the place of manufacture to the site of`
  line `erection and forward a report of the inspection along with the documents to the Chief Inspector within seven`
  line days.
  line
  line `(5) The Chief Inspector, on receipt of the report under sub-section (4), may---`
  line
  line `(a) register the boiler and assign a register number thereto either forthwith or after satisfying himself`
  line `that any structural alteration, addition or renewal which he may deem necessary has been made in or to the`
  line `boiler or any steam-pipe attached thereto; or`
  line
  line `(b) refuse to register the boiler:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Chief Inspector refuses to register a boiler, he shall forthwith communicate his`
  line `refusal to the owner of the boiler together with the reasons therefor.`
  line
  line `(6) The Chief Inspector shall, on registration of the boiler, order the grant of a certificate to the owner in`
  line `such form as may be specified by regulations, authorising the use of the boiler for a period not exceeding twelve`
  line `months, at a pressure not exceeding such maximum pressure as he thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where an economiser or an unfired boiler forms an integral part of such processing plant in`
  line `which steam is generated solely by the use of oil, asphalt or bitumen as a heating medium, the Chief Inspector`
  line `may authorise the use of such boiler for a period not exceeding twenty-four months.`
  line
  line `(7) The Inspector shall forthwith convey to the owner of the boiler the order of the Chief Inspector and shall`
  line `in accordance therewith, grant a certificate to the owner of which such grant has been ordered.`
  line
  line `(8) On receipt of the boiler registration certificate, the owner shall cause the register number to be`
  line `permanently marked on the boiler in such manner and within such time as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(9) The transfer of boilers from one place to another within a State shall be reported in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (96664)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Renewal of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96664&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) A certificate authorising the use of a boiler shall cease to be in force,---`
  line
  line `(a) on the expiry of the period for which it was granted; or`
  line
  line `(b) when any accident occurs to the boiler; or`
  line
  line `(c) when the boiler is moved, except a vertical boiler, the heating surface of which is less than`
  line `twenty square metres, or a portable or vehicular boiler; or`
  line
  line `(d) save as provided in section 17, when any structural alteration, addition or renewal is made in or`
  line `to the boiler; or`
  line
  line `(e) in case the Chief Inspector in any particular case so directs, when any structural alteration,`
  line `addition or renewal is made in or to any steam-pipe attached to the boiler; or`
  line
  line `(f) on the communication to the owner of the boiler of an order of the Chief Inspector or the`
  line `Inspector prohibiting its use on the ground that it or any boiler components attached to it is in a`
  line `dangerous condition.`
  line
  line `(2) An order made under clause (f) of sub-section (1) shall contain the grounds on which the order is`
  line `made and the same shall be communicated to the owner.`
  line
  line `(3) When a certificate ceases to be in force, the owner of the boiler may make an application to the`
  line `competent person for renewal thereof in such form, along with such documents and fee as may be specified`
  line `by regulations.`
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an application under sub-section (3), the competent person shall, within fifteen days`
  line `from the date of such receipt, inspect the boiler in such manner as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(5) If the competent person is,---`
  line
  line `(a) satisfied that the boiler and the boiler components attached thereto are in good condition, he`
  line `shall grant a certificate for such period as may be specified by regulations;`
  line
  line `(b) of the opinion that the boiler or boiler components, or both, does not conform to the standards`
  line `as may be specified by regulations, he may, for reasons to be recorded in writing, refuse to grant the`
  line `certificate:`
  line
  line `Provided that no certificate shall be refused unless the inspecting authority had directed the owner of`
  line `the boiler or the boiler components, or both, in writing to carry out such modifications or rectifications as`
  line `it deems necessary and the competent person is of the opinion that inspite of such direction, the owner of`
  line `the boiler or boiler components, or both, has not carried out the modifications or rectifications:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the competent person shall, within forty-eight hours of making the inspection`
  line `under sub-section (4), inform the owner of the boiler or boiler components, or both, any defect or deficiency`
  line `in his opinion and the reasons therefor and shall forthwith inform the Chief Inspector about such defect or`
  line deficiency.
  line
  line `(6) The Chief Inspector, on receipt of an information under sub-section (5), may, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act and the regulations made thereunder, order the renewal of the certificate on such`
  line `terms and conditions as may be specified by regulations or may refuse to renew it:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the Chief Inspector refuses to renew a certificate, he shall forthwith communicate`
  line `his refusal to the owner of the boiler, together with the reasons therefor.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to prevent an owner of a boiler from applying for a renewal`
  line `certificate therefor at any time during the currency of a certificate.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (96665)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Provisional order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96665&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Inspector reports the case of any boiler to the Chief Inspector`
  line `under sub-section (4) of section 12, he may, if the use of such boiler or its components is not prohibited`
  line `under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 13 as being in a dangerous condition, grant to the owner thereof`
  line `a provisional order in writing, permitting the boiler to be used at a pressure not exceeding such maximum`
  line `pressure as he thinks fit and in accordance with the regulations made under this Act, pending the receipt of`
  line `the order of the Chief Inspector.`
  line
  line `(2) Such provisional order shall cease to be in force---`
  line
  line `(i) on the expiry of six months from the date on which it is granted; or`
  line
  line `(ii) on receipt of the orders of the Chief Inspector; or`
  line
  line `(iii) in any of the cases referred to in clauses (b), (c), (d), (e) and (f) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 13,`
  line
  line `and on so ceasing to be in force, shall be surrendered to the Inspector.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (96666)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Use of boiler pending grant of certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96666&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 14, when the period of a certificate relating to a boiler has expired, the owner shall, subject to the`
  line `condition that he has applied for renewal before the expiry of the period for renewal of the certificate, be`
  line `entitled to use the boiler at the maximum pressure entered in that certificate pending the issue of orders on`
  line `the renewal application made under sub-section (3) of section 13.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (96667)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Revocation of certificate or provisional order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96667&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Inspector may at any time withdraw`
  line `or revoke any certificate or provisional order on the report of an Inspector or otherwise,---`
  line
  line `(a) if there is reason to believe that the certificate or provisional order has been obtained`
  line `fraudulently or has been granted erroneously or without sufficient examination; or`
  line
  line `(b) if the boiler in respect of which it has been granted has ceased to be in good condition; or`
  line
  line `(c) if the boiler is in the charge of a person not holding the certificate of proficiency or competency`
  line `referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 11.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (96668)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Alteration and renewal of boiler.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96668&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `No structural alteration, addition or renewal shall be made in`
  line `or to any boiler registered under this Act unless such alteration, addition or renewal has been authorised in`
  line `writing by the Chief Inspector:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such authorisation is required where the structural alteration, addition or renewal is`
  line `made under the supervision of a competent person.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (96669)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Alteration and renewal of steam-pipe or boiler components.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96669&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the owner of any boiler`
  line `registered under this Act intends to make any structural alteration, addition or renewal in or to any`
  line `steam-pipe or other boiler components attached to the boiler, he shall submit to the Chief Inspector a report`
  line `in writing of his intention and send therewith such particulars of proposed alteration, addition or renewal,`
  line `as may be specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) Any structural alteration, addition or renewal shall be made by a person possessing a boiler repairer`
  line `certificate under the supervision of the competent person.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (96670)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Duty of owner at examination.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96670&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) On any date fixed under this Act for the examination of a`
  line `boiler or boiler components, or both, the owner thereof shall be bound,---`
  line
  line `(a) to afford to the competent person all reasonable facilities for the examination and all such`
  line `information as may reasonably be required of him;`
  line
  line `(b) to have the boiler or boiler components, or both, properly prepared and ready for examination`
  line `in the such manner as may be specified by regulations; and`
  line
  line `(c) in case of an application for the registration of a boiler under sub-section (1) of section 12, to`
  line `provide to the competent person such drawing, specification, certificate and other particulars as may be`
  line `specified by regulations.`
  line
  line `(2) If the owner fails, without reasonable cause, to comply with the provisions of sub-section (1), the`
  line `competent person may refuse to make the examination and report the matter to the Chief Inspector who`
  line `shall, unless sufficient cause to the contrary is shown, require the owner to file a fresh application for`
  line `registration or renewal of certificate for use of boiler and may forbid him to use the boiler.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (96671)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Production of certificate and provisional order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96671&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The owner of any boiler who holds a certificate`
  line `or provisional order relating thereto shall, at all reasonable times during the period for which the certificate`
  line `or order is in force, be bound to produce the same when called upon to do so by the District Magistrate, the`
  line `Commissioner of Police or the Magistrate of the first class, having jurisdiction in the area in which the`
  line `boiler is for the time being located, or by the Chief Inspector or Inspector or by any Inspector appointed`
  line `under the Factories Act, 1948 (63 of 1948) or by any person specially authorised in writing by the District`
  line `Magistrate or the Commissioner of Police.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (96672)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Transfer of certificate and provisional order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96672&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Where any other person becomes the owner of a`
  line `boiler during the period for which a certificate or provisional order relating thereto is in force, the preceding`
  line `owner or his legal heirs shall be bound to make over to him the certificate or provisional order.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (96673)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Powers of entry of Inspector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96673&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `An Inspector may, for the purposes of inspecting or examining a`
  line `boiler or any steam-pipe attached thereto or to ensure the compliance of the provisions of this Act, rules`
  line `and regulations made thereunder, at all reasonable times, enter any place or building within the limits of`
  line `the area for which he has been appointed, in which he has reason to believe that a boiler is in use.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (96674)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Report of accident.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96674&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any accident occurs to a boiler or boiler components, the owner or`
  line `person in charge thereof shall within twenty-four hours of the accident, report the same in writing to the`
  line Inspector.
  line
  line `(2) Every such report shall contain a true description of the nature of the accident and of the injury, if`
  line `any, caused thereby to the boiler or to the boiler components or to any person, and be detailed in such`
  line `manner as to enable the Inspector to judge the gravity of the accident.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person shall be bound to answer truly to the best of his knowledge and ability every question`
  line `put to him in writing by the Inspector as to the cause, nature or extent of the accident.`
  line
  line `(4) The inquiry in respect of accident under this Act shall be made in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line `by the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any death has occurred due to any accident to a boiler or boiler components, an`
  line `inquiry may be conducted by such person and in such manner as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (96675)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Appeal to Chief Inspector.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96675&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by,---`
  line
  line `(a) an order made by an Inspector in exercise of any power conferred by or under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) a refusal by an Inspector to make any order or to grant any certificate which he is required or`
  line `empowered by or under this Act, to make or grant,`
  line
  line `may, within thirty days from the date on which such order or refusal is communicated to him, appeal against`
  line `the order or refusal to the Chief Inspector.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be made in such manner as may be prescribed by the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) The procedure for disposing of an appeal made under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (96676)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Appeal to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96676&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made under section 24`
  line `by the Chief Inspector---`
  line
  line `(a) refusing to register a boiler or to grant or renew a certificate in respect of a boiler;`
  line
  line `(b) refusing to grant a certificate having validity for the full period applied for;`
  line
  line `(c) refusing to grant a certificate authorising the use of a boiler at the maximum desired pressure;`
  line
  line `(d) withdrawing or revoking a certificate or provisional order;`
  line
  line `(e) reducing the amount of pressure indicated in any certificate or the period for which such certificate`
  line `has been granted;`
  line
  line `(f) ordering any structural alteration, addition or renewal to be made in or to a boiler or steam-pipe;`
  line or
  line
  line `(g) refusing sanction to the making of any structural alteration, addition or renewal to be made in or`
  line `to a boiler or steam-pipe,`
  line
  line `may, within thirty days of the communication to him of such order, prefer an appeal to the Central`
  line `Government in such form and manner, within such time and on payment of such fee as may be prescribed`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by the refusal of an inspecting authority to grant a certificate of inspection of`
  line `manufacture or erection may, within thirty days from the date of communication of such refusal, prefer an`
  line `appeal to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The procedure for disposing of an appeal shall be such as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (96677)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Application for revision of order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96677&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of the Central`
  line `Government made under section 25 may, within sixty days of the communication to him of such order,`
  line `make an application to the Central Government for a revision of its order.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application for revision of order under this section shall be made in such form and manner,`
  line `within such time and on payment of such fee as may be prescribed by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (96678)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Minor penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96678&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Any owner of a boiler who refuses or without reasonable excuse fails,---`
  line
  line `(i) to surrender a provisional order as required by sub-section (2) of section 14; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to produce a certificate or provisional order when duly called upon to do so under`
  line `section 20; or`
  line
  line `(iii) to make over to the new owner of a boiler a certificate or provisional order as required by`
  line `section 21; or`
  line
  line `(iv) to report an accident to a boiler or boiler components when so required under section 23,`
  line
  line `shall be liable to penalty which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (96679)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Penalties for illegal use of boiler.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96679&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Any owner of a boiler who,---`
  line
  line `(a) in any case in which a certificate or provisional order is required for the use of the boiler under`
  line `this Act, uses the boiler either without any such certificate or order, or at a higher pressure than that`
  line `allowed thereby; or`
  line
  line `(b) uses or permits to be used a boiler which has been transferred from one State to another without`
  line `such transfer having been reported as required under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 11; or`
  line
  line `(c) fails to cause the register number allotted to the boiler under this Act to be permanently marked`
  line `on the boiler as required under sub-section (8) of section 12,`
  line
  line `shall be liable to penalty which may extend to one lakh rupees and in the case of a continuing`
  line `contravention, with an additional penalty which may extend to one thousand rupees for each day after the`
  line `first day during which the contravention continues.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (96680)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Punishment for certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96680&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,---`
  line
  line `(a) makes any structural alteration, addition or renewal in or to a boiler without first obtaining the`
  line `authorisation of the Chief Inspector when so required by section 17, or to a steam-pipe without first`
  line `informing the Chief Inspector under section 18; or`
  line
  line `(b) tampers with a safety valve of a boiler so as to render it inoperative at the maximum pressure`
  line `at which the use of the boiler is authorised under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(c) allows another person to go inside a boiler without effectively disconnecting the same from`
  line `any steam or hot water connection with any other boiler or from fuel mains, in accordance with the`
  line `regulations made under this Act,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to two years or with fine which may extend to`
  line `one lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (96681)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Penalty for tampering with register mark.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96681&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever removes, alters, defaces, renders`
  line `invisible or otherwise tampers with the register number marked on a boiler in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Act, shall be liable to penalty which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever fraudulently marks upon a boiler a register number which has not been assigned to it under`
  line `this Act, shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to two years, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to one lakh rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (96682)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Penalty for breach of rules or regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96682&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Any rule or regulation made under this Act may`
  line `direct that a person contravening such rule or regulation shall be liable, in the case of a first contravention,`
  line `with penalty which may extend to one thousand rupees and in the case of any subsequent contravention,`
  line `with penalty which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (96683)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Recovery of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96683&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) All penalties, fines and costs levied under this Act shall be recoverable`
  line `as arrears of land-revenue.`
  line
  line `(2) The penalties, fines and costs levied under this Act shall be utilised in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed by the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (96684)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Limitation and previous sanction for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96684&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for an offence made`
  line `punishable by or under this Act shall be instituted except within twenty-four months from the date of the`
  line `commission of the offence and no such prosecution shall be instituted without the previous sanction of the`
  line `Chief Inspector.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (96685)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Trial of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96685&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `No offence made punishable by or under this Act shall be tried by a court`
  line `inferior to that of a Magistrate of the first class.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (96686)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Adjudication of penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96686&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government or the Union territory administration may,`
  line `for the purposes of determining the penalties under sections 27, 28, sub-section (1) of section 30 and`
  line `section 31, authorise the District Magistrate or the Additional District Magistrate having jurisdiction, to be`
  line `the adjudicating officer to hold an inquiry and impose penalty, in such manner as may be prescribed by the`
  line `State Government or the Central Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) The adjudicating officer may summon and enforce the attendance of any person acquainted with`
  line `the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to produce any document, which in the opinion`
  line `of the adjudicating officer, may be useful for, or relevant to, the subject-matter of the inquiry, and if, on`
  line `such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person concerned has failed to comply with any or all of the provisions`
  line `of section 27 or section 28 or sub-section (1) of section 30 or section 31, he may by an order, impose penalty`
  line `on such person stating therein the contravention:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such penalty shall be imposed without giving the person concerned a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (96687)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Appeal against orders of adjudicating officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96687&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by the order passed`
  line `by the adjudicating officer under section 35, may prefer an appeal to an officer not below the rank of`
  line `Secretary to the State Government or the Union territory administration specially authorised by that`
  line `Government or administration in this behalf, to be an appellate authority, within sixty days from the date`
  line `of receipt of the order, in such form and manner as may be prescribed by the State Government or the`
  line `Central Government, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal may be admitted after the expiry of the period of sixty days if the appellant satisfies the`
  line `appellate authority that he had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) The appellate authority may, after giving the parties to the appeal an opportunity of being heard,`
  line `pass such order as he may think fit.`
  line
  line `(4) An appeal under sub-section (1) shall be disposed of within sixty days from the date of filing of the`
  line appeal.
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (96688)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power of Central Government to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96688&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may give such`
  line `directions as it may deem necessary, to a State Government for carrying into effect any of the provisions to`
  line `this Act and the State Government shall comply with such directions.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (96689)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title Exemptions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96689&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification, exclude any area as may be`
  line `specified therein, from the operation of all or any of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may, by notification, exempt from the operation of this Act, subject to such`
  line `conditions and restrictions as it thinks fit, any boiler or class or type of boilers used exclusively for the`
  line `heating of buildings or the supply of hot water.`
  line
  line `(3) In case of any emergency, the State Government may, by general or special order in writing, exempt`
  line `any boiler or steam-pipe or any class of boilers or steam-pipes from the operation of all or any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) If the State Government is satisfied that having regard to the material, design or construction of`
  line `boilers and to the need for the rapid industrialisation of the country, it is necessary so to do, it may, by`
  line `notification and subject to such conditions as may be specified by regulations, exempt any boiler or boiler`
  line `components in the whole or any part of the State from the operation of all or any of the provisions of this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (96690)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96690&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the term of office of the members and the manner of their nomination under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) the qualifications and experience of Technical Adviser under sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the salary and allowances and terms and conditions of service of Technical Adviser under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) the qualifications and experience of Chief Inspector, Deputy Chief Inspectors and Inspectors`
  line `under sub-section (5) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(e) the boiler which shall be in the charge of persons holding certificate of proficiency or`
  line `competency under clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(f) the qualifications, experience, fee and the procedure for obtaining a certificate of proficiency or`
  line `competency under sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(g) the person who shall conduct inquiry and the manner of conducting such inquiry into the`
  line `accident causing death under the proviso to sub-section (4) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(h) the form, manner, time and fee for preferring appeal to the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(i) the procedure for disposing of an appeal under sub-section (3) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(j) the form, manner, time and fee for filing revision application under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 26;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of holding inquiry and imposing penalty under sub-section (1) of section 35;`
  line
  line `(l) the form and manner of preferring appeal under sub-section (1) of section 36.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (96691)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Power of Board to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96691&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board may, by notification and subject to the`
  line `condition of previous publication, make regulations not inconsistent with this Act and the rules made`
  line `thereunder, to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of recognition of person as competent person under clause (g) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of recognition of institution as inspecting authority under clause (j) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of recognition of competent authority under sub-section (1) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(d) the welders certificate under sub-section (2) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) the procedure for examination and grant of welders certificate under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) the other conditions and fee and for grant of welders certificate under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 6;`
  line
  line `(g) the facilities for design and construction of boiler and boiler components under clause (a) of`
  line `section 7;`
  line
  line `(h) the specifications for material, mounting and fitting used in the construction of boiler or boiler`
  line `components under clause (c) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(i) the stages of inspection during manufacture of boiler or boiler components by the inspecting`
  line `authority under sub-section (1) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(j) the procedure for inspection and certification of boiler or boiler components by the inspecting`
  line `authority under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(k) the standard for design and drawing of boiler or boiler components under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(l) the fee for inspection of boiler or boiler components during manufacture under sub-section (4)`
  line `of section 8;`
  line
  line `(m) the procedure for inspection and certification of a boiler or boiler components during erection`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(n) the standards for erection of a boiler; and the form of certificate of inspection under clause (a)`
  line `of sub-section (3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(o) the fee payable for inspection during erection under sub-section (4) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(p) the facilities for repairing of boiler and boiler components under clause (a) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 10;`
  line
  line `(q) the standards for design and drawings of the boiler or boiler components, and the specifications`
  line `for material, mounting and fitting used in the repair of the boiler or boiler components, under`
  line `clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(r) the measures for the safety of person working inside a boiler under clause (f) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 10;`
  line
  line `(s) the manner of obtaining a certificate under sub-section (2) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(t) the manner of reporting of transfer of boiler under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(u) the form along with the drawings, specification, certificate and other documents for registration`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(v) the form for grant of certificate to the owner authorising the use of the boiler under`
  line `sub-section (6) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(w) the manner and time in which the register number shall be marked on the boiler under`
  line `sub-section (8) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(x) the form, documents and fee for renewal of certificate under sub-section (3) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(y) the manner for inspection of the boiler under sub-section (4) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(z) the validity period of the certificate under clause (a) of sub-section (5) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(za) the standards for boiler or boiler components under clause (b) of sub-section (5) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(zb) the terms and conditions for the renewal of certificate under sub-section (6) of section 13;`
  line
  line `(zc) the particulars of proposed alteration, addition or renewal of steam-pipe and other boiler`
  line `components under sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(zd) the manner of preparation of the boiler or boiler components for examination under clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(ze) the drawing, specification, certificate and other particulars to be provided to the competent`
  line `person under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(zf) the manner of disconnecting the boiler under clause (c) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(zg) the conditions for exemption of any boiler or boiler components under sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 38;`
  line
  line `(zh) for any other matter relating to design, manufacture, erection and use of boiler and boiler`
  line `components which is to be regulated by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (96692)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96692&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made by the Central`
  line `Government under section 39 and every regulation made by the Board under section 40 shall be laid, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of`
  line `thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the`
  line `expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses`
  line `agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or both Houses agree that the rule or regulation`
  line `should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of`
  line `no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without`
  line `prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (96693)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96693&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification and`
  line `subject to the condition of previous publication, make rules not inconsistent with this Act and regulations`
  line `made thereunder for all or any of the following provisions, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the powers and duties of the Chief Inspector, Deputy Chief Inspectors and Inspectors under subsection (8) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the fee payable for registration of boiler under sub-section (2) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(c) the period within which Inspector shall be required to examine the boiler under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner of reporting transfer of boilers from one place to another within State under`
  line `sub-section (9) of section 12;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of inquiry in respect of an accident under sub-section (4) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner for making appeals under sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(g) the procedure for disposing of appeals under sub-section (3) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which the penalties, fines and costs levied under this Act shall be utilised under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 32;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of holding inquiry and imposing penalty under sub-section (1) of section 35; and`
  line
  line `(j) the form and manner of preferring appeal under sub-section (1) of section 36.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the State Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is`
  line `made, before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (96694)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Finality of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96694&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `An order of the Central Government under sections 25 and 26, or of the Chief`
  line `Inspector, or of a Deputy Chief Inspector, or of an Inspector, shall be final and shall not be called in question`
  line `in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (96695)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96695&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions, not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for removing`
  line `the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of three years from the date of`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (96696)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044&sectionId=96696&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_61_00011_A2025-12_1748411048044
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Boilers Act, 1923 (5 of 1923) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal,---`
  line
  line `(a) any notification, rule, regulation, bye-law, order or exemption issued, made or granted under`
  line `the Act so repealed shall have effect as if it had been issued, made or granted under the provisions of`
  line `this Act, till new notification, rule, regulation, bye-law, order or exemption is issued, made or granted`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) any office established or created, officer appointed and any body constituted under the Act so`
  line `repealed shall continue and shall be deemed to have been established, created, appointed or constituted`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) any document referring to the Act so repealed shall be construed as referring to this Act or to`
  line `the provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) any fine or penalty levied under the Act so repealed may be recovered as if it had been levied`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) any offence committed under the Act so repealed may be prosecuted and punished as if it had`
  line `been committed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) any boiler registered under the Act so repealed shall be deemed to have been registered under`
  line `this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) any certificate of competency or proficiency, exemption, or any other certificate or document`
  line `issued, made or granted under the Act so repealed and in force at the commencement of this Act shall`
  line `be deemed to have been issued, made or granted under this Act and shall, unless cancelled under this`
  line `Act, continue in force until the date shown in the certificate or document, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(h) any proceeding pending before any court under the Act so repealed may be tried or disposed of`
  line `under the corresponding provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(i) any inspection, investigation or inquiry ordered to be done under the provisions of the Act so`
  line `repealed shall continue to be proceeded with as if such inspection, investigation or inquiry is ordered`
  line `to be done under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The mention of particular matters in this section shall not be held to prejudice or affect the general`
  line `application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), with regard to the effect of repeals.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding the repeal of the aforesaid Act, the Board constituted under the Act so repealed`
  line `shall continue to function till a new Board is constituted under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
